==English==
===Etymology===
Persian, from Arabic [[حافظ]] ''ʜāfiẓ'', present participle of [[حفظ]] ''ʜafiẓa'' ‘to guard, know by heart’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hɑ:fɪz/

===Noun===
'''hafiz'''
# a [[Muslim]] who knows the [[Qur’an]] off by heart
#:*'''2001''': He was a '''hafiz''', one who knows the Qur’an by heart, and he sang it in a slow, simple chant. — Yann Martel, ''Life of Pi''

